---
title: Lemon Za’atar Chicken with Green Goddess Dressing, Turmeric Quinoa, & Honey Roasted Carrots
description: Za’atar is one of those spices that adds a bit of flare (and a whole lot of flavor) to pretty much any dish. Tonight, it’s dressing up chicken, marinated in a mix of the spice and lemon juice, for a tangy treat. We’re also seasoning quinoa with turmeric and roasted carrots with honey and lemon zest on the side. This meal is about to spice up your life.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/lemon-zaatar-chicken-f822018f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/lemon-zaatar-chicken-60eef023f0590e4f0a2baa83-e5a49dfd.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 810 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lemon-zaatar-chicken-60eef023f0590e4f0a2baa83
cuisine: Middle East
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} into long, thin sticks (ours were 3 inches long and 1/3 inch wide). Finely chop @parsley{}(chopped) and @chives{}(chopped).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Add to a #medium bowl{} along with @za'atar spice{1%tablespoon}, juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Turn chicken to coat. Set aside to marinate.

In a #small pot{}, combine 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{2}, half the garlic, half the @turmeric{1%teaspoon} (all for 4), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then stir in @white quinoa{1/2%cup}; cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until quinoa is tender and liquid has evaporated, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While quinoa cooks, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}; season with salt and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While carrots roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, parsley, chives, juice from remaining lemon, 1/2 tsp water, and remaining garlic to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Drizzle roasted carrots with @honey{2%teaspoon} and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Sprinkle with lemon zest to taste; toss on sheet to coat.

> TIP: We recommend using tongs here.

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{} and season with salt (we used 1/4 tsp; 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) and pepper.

> TIP: For extra richness, stir in 1 TBSP butter.

Divide quinoa between plates. Top with lemon za'atar chicken and drizzle with green goddess dressing. Serve honey roasted carrots on the side.